2026-04-16 07:49:15 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Power supply output cables', 'Control module input cables'] hypothesis_explanation='The symptoms observed (main lamp does not turn on, power supply indicator LED on, control module red LED on) are consistent with a polarity inversion between the power supply and the control module. The red LED in the control module is specifically designed to indicate this situation. The visual inspection confirmed that the power supply output cables are connected to the control module inputs with inverted polarity (+ to − and − to +). This prevents current from correctly reaching the lamp load due to the orientation of the load module diode, and triggers the control module inversion indicator. Correcting this polarity inversion should restore normal operation.'
